<br>
Also, can anyone give advice on the best way to get my research skill up as quickly as possible?<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
<br>
Apokk<br>
24 Wizard<br>
Xev Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udzenari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dzenari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/25/01 10:15:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting?</span><hr size=1> First quad kiting doesn't really become effective until you reach 34th and you have two specific spells, bonds of force and circle of force.  With bonds you can snare 4 mobs at a time and with cirlce you can hit them for about 215pts of damage each.<br>
<br>
The first thing you have to do is round up the mobs, if you don't have sow or jboots, you'll need one or the other in order to outrun most mobs.  You might be able to outrun spectres without either.  In order to round them up simply run around them in circles until you have a cluster.  Once they're grouped together cast bonds of force, if you're lucky you'll snare all four.  Then simply run away from them and get a good enough distance to cast circle of force and viola you're quad kiting. <p>Dzenari Darktear<br>
<i>Wizard of Innoruuk</i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uprincetoneci.showPublicProfile?language=EN>princeton eci</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/25/01 4:02:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting?</span><hr size=1> Here's a couple tips that worked for me:<br>
<br>
1. Practice on greenies<br>
<br>
2. Start with snaring the exact same monster (don't try mixed groups to start out with)<br>
<br>
3. A second AoE caster (like a dr00d) in a 2 person group can help you get technique down without dying <p><B>Princeton</B><BR>
44th Wizzie<BR>
E'ci <I>Lords of Light</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umojojojoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mojojojoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/25/01 10:56:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://i5.yimg.com/5/a490876c/h/2abcb073/viagport.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting?</span><hr size=1> Actually @ 24 you have an excellent spot to learn to quad and get AWESOME xp at the same time, provided you can get Sow, which is pretty ez in LOIO...<br>
<br>
This was how I learned, leveled to 31:<br>
In Loio, there are 4 pillars lakeside in between the Sarnak Fort and the Gobbie House.  Lev yourself, and bind yourself on top of one of the back pillars.  This is your safe med spot.  Now med to full, load your 24 AOE, and a low DD (i used shock of ice) and a high DD.  Skin yourself, Shield yourself, med to full.  At full mana, invis yourself and run to the Gobbie House.  Facing the shore, the GH is to your right, just off shore.  There is a 4 spawn in there that is almost never camped.  Target the farthest gobbie from you, and cast your low DD on him.  Start backing away, as all 4 will come.  Run around them, herding them into a ball.  Try to run towards the FV zone, as the mobs there are lower level and will not agro you.  Then when you have them all balled, run away for a few secs till your just out of casting range (you'll learn how far/long pretty quick).  Chain push your cast button, while rotating yourself to prevent interupts, till it goes of, and wait for it to hit.  As soon as it hits, repeat the run outta range and cast.  When only one is left, give him the appropriate DD spell, or melee him if you are good enuf at it.  YOU WILL DIE LEARNING HOW TO DO THIS.  I died 3x before I got it, then didnt die again until I tried grouping <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   When this xp is too slow for your liking, or you have alot of xtra mana, try the towers at the forts back door.  These have at least 2 sarnaks, and if youre smart, you can wrangle 4 w/o pulling an adherent (they sow so be careful of them and the mobs they've sow'd).  Personally, I've found bonds of force to be overrated.  As long as I'm SoW'd, I wont get hit, unless there's a lag spike.  Timing is crucial, as is courage <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Hope this helps you!<br>
 <p><img src="http://i5.yimg.com/5/a490876c/h/c4a8207c/viagro.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujmillican.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jmillican</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/01 10:54:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting?</span><hr size=1> The best way to get your research skill is to practise it at your local guild (ie. buy it up).  I am a lvl 39 wiz and have my research skill maxed out.  Sure it cost me a couple hundred platinum and so what?  Money to a Wiz is easy to get if from porting if nothing else.  Its quick and painless and now I rarely fail in combining runes.<br>
<br>
Phileep Majere of Eci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uabc123def456.showPublicProfile?language=EN>abc123def456</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/01 9:59:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> specs...</span><hr size=1> I am a 53 wizard and started aoe kiting specs for money for peridots and also killin SG's for money too (and also to practice kiting and gaining soem green exp).... is it true bonds of force only stacks up on 4 mobs at same time? how about atols spectral shackles? how many can THAT spell stack up on mobs? i still use bonds cause its less mana and they usually die before it wears off...    its fun seeing 4-5 specs lined up dead scattering the land of oasis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unoonanie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Noonanie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 10:09:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Last thing...</span><hr size=1> <br>
One thing no one seems to tell you...<br>
<br>
Get to know the area!<br>
<br>
Spend some time and find a good spot.  One that meets your<br>
requirements.  Keep an eye out for what sorts of mobs wander<br>
around and where they path through.<br>
<br>
Be aware of other players in your area.  So you don't <br>
accidentally train them... and so they don't interfere with<br>
a Wizard's Master Plan.  Besides... if they're a group...<br>
maybe they got a Chanter that'll C you... or a Dr00d/Shammie/Ranger that'll sow you.<br>
<br>
Location, Location, Location... just as important as the<br>
rest of your tactics.<br>
<br>
Best of luck.<br>
<br>
Lasservien Leadbottom<br>
lvl 56 Evoker - Silent Shadows<br>
Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=40.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=41.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=22.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=22.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm27">PVP Forum<option value="graffeswiz